[Internet]
|
(Host Internet) -- VirtualBox NAT
|
pfSense VM (Adapter1:NAT -> WAN, Adapter2: Internal -> LAN: labnet)
|
Internal Network (labnet)
├── Kali VM (Internal)
└── Ubuntu Server VM (Internal) -> Safeline app

pfSense handles NAT, DHCP, DNS, firewall rules, and optional IDS/IPS (Suricata).

Kali and Ubuntu live on an Internal Network (e.g., labnet) and never bridge directly to the host LAN.

Safeline runs on the Ubuntu VM (or in a container on the Ubuntu VM).
